Sony Music Greece’s Website Hacked, Compromising Data of 8,500 Customers

-- B y   M a r i k o   Y a s u
-- 
2011-05-24T08:22:27Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-24/sony-music-greece-s-website-hacked-compromising-data-of-8-500-customers.html
Sony Corp. (6758)  said the website of its
music unit in  Greece  was hacked, compromising the personal
information of about 8,500 customers registered as fans of its
artists.  The third-party operator of Sony Music Entertainment
Greece’s website discovered the breach on May 22 and took down
the site, Atsuo Omagari, a Tokyo-based Sony spokesman, said by
phone today.  The information includes names, e-mail addresses and phone
numbers but not credit card data, the spokesman said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Mariko Yasu in Tokyo at 
 myasu@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Kyung Bok Cho at 
 kcho7@bloomberg.net  